---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import '../../styles/legal.css';
---
<Layout
  title="Support — EDU Mileage+"
  description="Help and support for EDU Mileage+. Email support@eduplusapps.com or browse common topics: tracking setup, iCloud sync, subscriptions, and more."
  showNav={false}
  showFooter={false}
>
<div class="legal-page">

<header>
  <div class="app-name">EDU Plus Apps</div>
  <h1>Support</h1>
  <div class="meta">EDU Mileage+ &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; Help &amp; Contact</div>
</header>

<main>

  <section>
    <p>EDU Mileage+ is built and supported by a single developer. Most questions are answered fastest by the in-app Help section, but you're always welcome to email directly.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Email Support</h2>
    <div class="contact-block centered">
      <div class="label">Get in touch</div>
      <a class="email" href="mailto:support@eduplusapps.com">support@eduplusapps.com</a>
      <p class="note">Replies typically within 1–2 business days.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>In-App Help</h2>
    <p>EDU Mileage+ includes a built-in Help section covering setup, tracking, reports, subscriptions, and troubleshooting.</p>
    <div class="info-box">
      <strong>Open it in the app:</strong> Settings tab → Help. Browse 7 topics with detailed answers to common questions.
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Common Topics</h2>
    <ul class="topic-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Tracking isn't working</strong>
        <span>Make sure Location permission is set to <em>Always</em> in Settings → EDU Mileage+ → Location, and that the app is running during your scheduled work hours.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>I need to recover my data</strong>
        <span>Open Settings → Data → iCloud Sync to check sync status. Your trips, sites, and reports sync to your private iCloud account automatically. To recover after reinstalling the app, tap <em>Restore from iCloud</em> on the Welcome screen.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Subscription &amp; billing</strong>
        <span>Subscriptions are managed by Apple. Open Settings → [Your Name] → Subscriptions on your iPhone to view, change, or cancel.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Restore Purchases</strong>
        <span>If your subscription isn't recognized after reinstalling, open the app's Subscription screen and tap <em>Restore Purchases</em>.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Adding a second district</strong>
        <span>Settings → Manage Districts → +. The District Add-On subscription unlocks a second district for $1.99/month, on top of the one included with your base subscription.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Deleting your account</strong>
        <span>To permanently remove all your data from this device and your iCloud account, open Settings → Delete Account in the app. This deletes your profile, trips, reports, districts, sites, and all related data after you confirm. The action cannot be undone.</span>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Privacy &amp; data</strong>
        <span>EDU Mileage+ has no servers. Trip data, GPS routes, and personal info live only on your device and in your private iCloud. See the <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</span>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Reporting Bugs</h2>
    <p>When emailing about a bug, the following details help fix it faster:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>iPhone model and iOS version (Settings → General → About)</li>
      <li>App version (Settings → About in EDU Mileage+)</li>
      <li>What you were doing when the issue happened</li>
      <li>Whether it's reproducible — does it happen every time?</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Feature Requests</h2>
    <p>Ideas are welcome. Email <a href="mailto:support@eduplusapps.com">support@eduplusapps.com</a> with what you'd like to see and how it would help your workflow.</p>
  </section>

</main>

<footer class="page-footer">
  <p>&copy; 2026 EDU Plus Apps &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; <a href="/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a></p>
</footer>

</div>
</Layout>
